parameters:
Alicia: Hello everyone, it's been a while. Please look forward to our
next game "Ray of the Floating Magic City - The Direct Descendant
Magician". Ray was developed using "Tsukuru ACE", wasn't it? I heard
that Ray was in production before Luuna and had a longer development
period due to certain circumstances.

Alicia: Since "Tsukuru ACE" cannot be adapted for smartphone games,
"Ray of the Floating Magic City - The Direct Descendant Magician" will
only be available for PC. When you want to play Ray, please make sure
to purchase it for your computer.

Ceres: Yo, we meet again. Look forward to the Knights of Messiah
making an appearance in the next title "Ray of the Floating Magical
City – The Direct Descendant Magician".

Ceres: But man, it feels like I'm always cleaning up after Rinny...
Writing reports and all... *sigh*. I'm going to get scolded by the
king and Hades again.
Rinny: ...

Rinny: Hmph... To think the reward for a gold medal and a complete
clear would be such a trivial afterword room. Well, it seems two types
of costume changes have been added. Utterly trivial indeed.

Rinny: Like I've said before, I'm no hero. I'll cut down anything
ugly. If that means Ceres has to write up a report, so be it. That
suits her just fine.

Rinny: Oh yeah, did you notice my icon sprite got a remake? Look
forward to seeing me in the next game.

Maya: Hello, long time no see! In our next title "Ray of the Floating
Magic City - The Direct Descendant Magician -", the Knights of Messiah
might make an appearance. Looking forward to it!

Maya: Also, please look forward to the naughty game featuring me, Lady
Alicia, and Rinny, Messiah IF! "Messiah IF" is a spin-off game of
"Messiah - The True Answer -".

[Jedite] Congratulations on the complete clear. It's been about three
years since Knights of Messiah went on sale (2019). Time flies so
quickly. Thank you for your unwavering support.

Luuna: Congratulations on the complete clear. Wow, getting all the
gold medals is quite impressive.

Luuna: Even if it's just in the epilogue room, I'm so happy to be able
to meet you, Satori, and Lord Ceres again.

[Satori] Congratulations on the complete clear. Who am I, you ask? If
you've forgotten, why not play again to find out~.

Riku: "Why am I here? Because I was one of the original members of
Messiah IF. I'm so happy to be with Maya again~."

[gyu] Thank you always for your support. Congratulations on achieving
a complete clear plus a gold medal in Luuna!

[gyu] As for my thoughts on the production of Luuna... "It was hell"
is the only way to put it; I went through quite an ordeal... There was
a circumstance and a goal to release it within the year 2022, and I'm
writing this on the very day of the game's sales registration...

[gyu] To have made it this far in such a short period of time feels
almost like a miracle. I've never felt so helped by so many people in
any other project as I did this time.

[gyu] For a project of this scale, it would normally be a three-year
production course, but considering the rushed speed at which we
worked, it went relatively smoothly. RPG creation is truly
difficult... and this time was incredibly challenging. It seems
unlikely that I'll ever get used to making RPGs.

[gyu] As for my thoughts on Luuna... Initially, Luuna was created as a
protagonist with the premise of being defeated by Lucia.

[gyu] But along the way, I changed my mind. I wanted her to be smiling
in the end. Perhaps I ended up projecting my emotions onto Luuna.

[gyu] The next work will be "Rade," but Rade is the complete opposite
of Luuna, a "dropout." Please look forward to how such a Rade will
interact with Lucia and Regnus Grahardt in the next work.

[gyu] I'm glad that this work allowed me to convey the details of the
setting, such as Lucia and others.

[gyu] Thank you from the bottom of my heart for playing Luuna. I truly
appreciate it. Please also look forward to the next work, "The
Floating Magical City of Rade ~The Direct Descendant Magician~" (ACE).

[gyu] Thank you so very much for enjoying it to this extent. You've
done an amazing job. Let's meet again in the next work!
Rinka: Meow~
